Linux terminal Commands

- sudo - super user permissions
- sudo apt-get install 
- cd ~ - change Directory to Home Directory
- cd ..
- cd .
- cd /
- scp 
- ssh root@IP 
- mkdir
- ./fileName.sh - executes the given program
- ls - show contents of current directory
- ls -a - [-a] show the hidden files and directories also
- pwd (print working directory) - tells the current directory name

- whoami - tells the name of the current log

Home Directory : ~
Root Directory : /


copy file to remote server:
scp -r /path/to/my/files root@0.0.0.0:/path/on/remote/droplet

